    "verdict_line": "DRAFT NEGLIGIBLE (upper-bound only; in-graph residual ~null) / VERIFY MISTUNED (bit-identical slack). DRAFT (M=1, headline): bit-identical (warps/stages-only) speedup 1.03x (sliding h256) / 1.03x (global h512); TPS off 481.53 is a band +0.056% (realistic-low, kanna #264's ~3.3us in-graph SDPA residual) .. +1.28% (upper bound, 75us standalone x K=7) -> NULL. VERIFY (M>1): a REAL bit-identical 1.10x/1.09x/1.09x (M8/16/32) from num_stages 3->2 on the head-512 verify SDPA (maxdiff=0.0; real wrapper == forced-s3 baseline, validated) -> recoverable slack for land #245 / denken #257. Greedy+PPL UNCHANGED by construction (warp/stage scheduling only).",
    "handoff_line": "the deployed TRITON_ATTN SDPA is NOT shape-specialized for Gemma-4's 256/512 head dims (bare @triton.jit, triton-default warps=4 / num_stages=3 -- validated: the real wrapper's wall-clock == our forced-s3 baseline to <1%), confirming the lever lawine #246's forced-TRITON_ATTN opens. On the DRAFT path (M=1, x K=7, the headline) the deployed config is already at/near its bit-identical tuned floor: warps/stages-only nets 1.03x (sliding) / 1.03x (global) but the in-graph draft SDPA is tiny (kanna #264 leaves ~3.3us after MLP/qo/io/head), so even the standalone UPPER-BOUND gain is +1.28% and the realistic-low is +0.056% off 481.53 -> NULL. On the VERIFY path (M in 8/16/32) there IS real bit-identical slack: forcing num_stages=2 (vs the deployed default 3) is 1.10/1.09/1.09x faster per-call on the head-512 verify SDPA, maxdiff=0.0 (greedy+PPL safe) -- a config the served launch could pass for the M>1 head-512 path. A larger TILE_SIZE/BLOCK_M (fp-tol, NOT bit-identical, maxdiff~3-6e-5) reaches +7.00% on the draft path but re-tiles the online softmax (lawine #246 risk) -> needs a measured greedy+PPL gate, NOT a config flip. [kanna: the MLP is the OTHER ~50% of the draft pass; denken #257: the verify num_stages=2 win is the autotunable part of verify_us(M) -- price it against the attention share; land #245: the M8/16/32 num_stages=2 config is a bit-identical step saving for the live tree-verify build.]"
